## ✅ DO's

| # | Do This | Why It Matters |
|---|---------|----------------|
| 1 | Keep your profile professional and updated | Recruiters and internship coordinators check social media |
| 2 | Share your learning achievements, projects, and certifications | Builds your digital identity and impresses future employers |
| 3 | Use privacy settings to control who sees your posts and stories | Protects your personal data from strangers |
| 4 | Think before posting — ask: Is it true? Is it kind? Is it necessary? | Prevents regret and protects your reputation |
| 5 | Give credit to original creators when sharing their content | Respects intellectual property and ethical standards |
| 6 | Engage respectfully with peers, seniors, and professionals | Builds a positive online reputation and network |
| 7 | Use strong, unique passwords for every social media account | Prevents hacking and unauthorized access |
| 8 | Report harmful, abusive, or fake content using platform tools | Makes the internet safer for everyone |

---

## ❌ DON'Ts

| # | Never Do This | Why It's Harmful |
|---|---------------|-----------------|
| 1 | Post offensive, hateful, or discriminatory content | Can lead to serious academic and legal consequences |
| 2 | Share personal details publicly — phone number, address, college ID | Makes you vulnerable to scams, stalking, and fraud |
| 3 | Engage in cyberbullying, trolling, or spreading rumors | Causes mental harm to others and damages your own reputation |
| 4 | Click on unknown links or ads received via DMs or posts | High risk of phishing, malware, and account theft |
| 5 | Post or share unverified news and misinformation | Spreads panic and can have legal consequences |
| 6 | Use your college/institution email to sign up for personal apps | Mixing personal and professional accounts creates security risks |
| 7 | Post negative comments about teachers, college, or classmates | Can affect your academic record and future opportunities |
| 8 | Share exam papers, internal documents, or confidential information | Violates college policy and can lead to disciplinary action |

